name: integer_i32_zero
description: |
  Zero is the i32 additive identity and the critical invalid divisor for
  integer division and remainder. Pairing it with one exercises divide-by-zero
  handling across fixed-width integer implementations.
format: hex
decode-as: i32-le
pair:
  - with: one.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i32"
  - "zero"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "remainder-by-zero"
  - "baseline"
---
00 00 00 00   # 0
